Class DJIInspireMainController

        • dji.sdk.api.MainController.DJIInspireMainController

  • public class DJIInspireMainController
extends DJIMainController

    DJI Inspire Main Controller Class

    Extending the DJIMainController, DJIInspireMainController is designed for Inspire 1 and Phantom 3. DJIMainController provides a series of information and status about the drone. Customers could monitor the instant message by using this class. Every 1000ms, the callback of MainController would send back the message the drone contains.

    Also, the mainController requires that developers correctly construct the life cycle. There is a tutorial for setting up the life cycle.

    private DJIMcuUpdateStateCallBack mMcuUpdateStateCallBack = null;

      DJIDrone.getDjiMC().startUpdateTimer(1000);
    }

    protected void onPause() {
      //other statements
      DJIDrone.getDjiMC().stopUpdateTimer();
    }

      • startUpdateTimer

        public boolean startUpdateTimer(int interval)
        Start upating timer and set the interval between each update. The timer will request information of main controller status, deform status and Error status. Developer could use setDeformInfoCallBack, setMcuUpdateStateCallBack and setMcuErrorCallBack to set up the action while sdk receives the data.
        Please note that the interval could not be lower than 100ms.
        Overrides:
        startUpdateTimer in class DJIMainController
        Parameters:
        interval - Timer run interval
        Returns:
        true for successfully starting Update timer.
            false for informing failure.
        See Also:
        DJIMainController.startUpdateTimer(int), DJIMainController.startUpdateTimer(int), dji.sdk.api.MainController.DJIMcErrorType, DJIMainControllerSystemState, DJIDeformInfo, setDeformInfoCallBack(DJIMcDeformInfoCallBack), setMcuUpdateStateCallBack(DJIMcuUpdateStateCallBack), setMcuErrorCallBack(DJIMcuErrorCallBack)
